    "The action of preventing, hindering, or interrupting production of another action or thought that would otherwise have happened.",
    "In psychology, the term refers to a voluntary or involuntary restraint that prevents or hinders the direct expression of an impulse, cognitive process, or action.",
    "In the neural / computational domain, it refers to a mechanism whereby one component of a network prevents or reduces activation of another component.",
